HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 208
By Reneau
A RESOLUTION to congratulate Jayme Salisbury on winning two
gold medals at the 2025 Tennessee Special
Olympics Winter Games.
WHEREAS, we are pleased to recognize those exemplary athletes who, through their
marvelous exploits, bring great honor and acclaim to Tennessee and serve as exceptional
ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy athlete is Jayme Salisbury, who recently won two gold
medals in the 2025 Tennessee Special Olympics Winter Games in Gatlinburg; and
WHEREASA, a part of the Orange Grove Center family in Chattanooga, Jayme
Salisbury won gold medals in both the snowboard slalom and snowboard giant slalom events,
despite having only practiced snowboarding once before the competition; and
WHEREAS, the games, held from January 26-28, 2025, featured 300 athletes from
across the State competing in four Special Olympic sports; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Salisbury, who is involved in programs at the Rossville Center, one of
Orange Grove's Georgia sites, has been competing in Special Olympics since he was in first or
second grade, competing in sports such as soccer, bowling, and flag football; and
WHEREAS, continuing to showcase his athletic talents, he is currently a member of
Orange Grove's basketball team; and
WHEREAS, Jayme Salisbury is coached by Kay McDowell and enjoys the loving support
and additional coaching of his mother, Kristi Salisbury, who described her son's performance as
a testament to his tenacity; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Salisbury has etched his name into the annals of Tennessee sports
history; his dedication, determination, work ethic, and talent not only made possible a successful
